# SENTINEL Frontend — Claude Code Instructions

You are working on the **frontend** of SENTINEL, an adversarial AI court for police
bodycam analysis. Backend is **complete and frozen** in `/opt/sentinel/`.

## Read first
- `/opt/sentinel/README.md` — product context, sponsor roles
- `/opt/sentinel/results/live/us_video3_session.json` — canonical session shape
- `/opt/sentinel/main.py` — SSE endpoints `/api/live/sessions`, `/api/live/replay/{id}`
- `./public/samples/*.json` — 5 demo sessions (mirrored from backend)

## Tech stack (fixed)
Next.js 16 App Router · TypeScript · Tailwind v4 · shadcn/ui · Zustand
· Framer Motion · lucide-react · native EventSource for SSE. No TanStack Query,
no wavesurfer, no particles. Always-dark theme.

## Design language
Corporate-restrained, not flashy. Reference: Linear, Stripe Atlas, Vercel.
- Background: deep graphite, not pure black
- Primary: emerald `#00B86B` (slightly darker than the typical AI-startup neon)
- Role colors: prosecution red, defense blue, judge gold, transcription teal
- Glass effect ONLY on overlay surfaces (VerdictCard, LiveBanner, modals, nav).
  NEVER on transcript or long lists — readability first.
- Sans: Geist. Mono: Geist Mono. No serif.
- Motion: spring(200, 22) for entries, ease-out 300ms for micro. No infinite anims.

## Pages
- `/` — Landing: hero (split-screen bidirectional), stat band, architecture
  diagram, jurisdictions tiles, sponsor strip, footer
- `/demo` — picker grid of 5 demo cases, `us_video3` featured
- `/demo/[sessionId]` — main artifact. Three columns: BodycamPlayer +
  TranscriptPane (left), VerdictCard + VisionCard + AlertsFeed + DeepScanFeed
  (right). LiveBanner absolute top.
- `/methodology` — technical explainer (P2)

## Key behaviors
- SSE via `EventSource` to `${NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE}/api/live/replay/{id}`
- Deep link: `/demo/us_video3?autoplay=instant&speed=10`
- Sponsor `(?)` tooltips on each major component citing model/provider
- BodycamPlayer uses HTML5 `<video>` from `/media/{session_id}.mp4`,
  gracefully hides if 404
- LiveBanner colored by `ruleSubject(rule_id)` — officer=red, citizen=gold,
  mutual=blue

## Demo sessions (in public/samples/)
- us_video3 — officer_at_fault HIGH (1A retaliation, Vision flipped verdict) ★featured
- us_aggression — officer_justified low (citizen drags officer)
- us_video2_vision — officer_justified none (drugs, probable cause)
- us_video1 — officer_justified none (force justified)
- it_domestic — officer_justified none (EU jurisdiction)

## Do NOT
- No auth, no upload UI, no admin panel
- No mobile layout for /demo (desktop only, show hint on mobile)
- No light theme toggle
- No analytics, no cookies banner
- No serif fonts, no emoji as load-bearing UI (only as labels like 🎥 for Vision)

## File structure expected
See full spec in repo README. Key folders:
- `app/` — routes
- `components/{shared,marketing,demo-picker,audit}/`
- `lib/{types,stores,hooks}/`
- `public/{samples,logos,media}/`

## Workflow
1. Generate TypeScript types from `public/samples/us_video3_session.json` into
   `lib/types/session.ts` — this is the single source of truth.
2. Build Zustand store + SSE hook.
3. Build `/demo/[sessionId]` with mock data first (read JSON directly), THEN
   wire SSE.
4. Build Landing.
5. Build Demo Picker.
6. Polish, deploy.

Always run `npm run dev` to verify each change. When TS errors appear, fix
them before moving on. Don't accumulate broken state.

## Architecture model — three temporal layers

The right column visualizes three layers operating at different cadences.
UI must make hierarchy visible: Verdict dominates.

- Layer 1 — Rapid Alerts (sub-second, per utterance). AlertsFeed + LiveBanner.
- Layer 2 — Deep Scans (every 10 utt OR 60s). DeepScanFeed, expandable items.
- Layer 3 — Live Verdict (debounced ~2-3s). VerdictCard, HERO position.

Visual weight: VerdictCard > LiveBanner > DeepScanFeed > AlertsFeed.
Never render all four with equal weight.

## Data types

All session/event types are defined in `lib/types/session.ts`, generated
from real backend JSON. NEVER redefine — always `import type` from there.
Field names are snake_case and frozen. Never camelCase, never invent fields.

## Demo UX

- `/demo/[sessionId]` autostarts replay on mount (no button click).
- Speed via `?speed=` query (1|2|4|10|instant), default 10.
- "Replay · pre-computed session" badge top-left (honest disclosure).
- Featured: `us_video3` (officer_at_fault HIGH, vision flipped verdict).

## Bidirectional UX (political safety)

- Picker shows ≥2 `officer_justified` cases alongside `officer_at_fault`.
- Never "catches misconduct" / "police misconduct AI" — use "audit layer",
  "adversarial review", "both sides".
- Verdict labels stay neutral: `officer_at_fault`, not `officer_guilty`.
- Alert border color: red=officer, gold=citizen, blue=mutual.

## Sponsor attribution

Each major component (VerdictCard, AlertsFeed, DeepScanFeed, VisionCard,
TranscriptPane) has a small (?) icon top-right opening a glass-light
tooltip. Exact tooltip text provided per-component in task prompts.
Footer: "Built on Speechmatics · Featherless · Google Gemini · Vultr".

## Responsive

- `/` and `/demo` picker — mobile-first (375 / 768 / 1280).
- `/demo/[sessionId]` — desktop only. Show overlay below 1280px:
  "SENTINEL Demo requires a desktop browser (≥1280px)."

## Anti-patterns — DO NOT

- No gradient text (bg-clip-text). Use solid colors with weight contrast.
- No glassmorphism on dense content (transcript, feeds). Solid surfaces.
- No pulsing/glowing CTAs.
- No auto-playing background video on landing.
- No "AI-powered" copy. Show, don't tell.
- No light-mode toggle.
- No emojis in headings/CTAs (only functional labels: ⚖️ 🎥).
- No confetti, no cookie banners, no "Made with ❤️".